christensen distinguished lecture slavoj zizek events at stanford christensen distinguished lecture slavoj zizek facebook twitter email print add to calendar hollywood beyond ideology enough has been written about hollywood as the ultimate ideological machine what about all those hollywood products which undermine the hegemonic ideology they are to be found also where one would not expect it from old neglected masterpieces frankenheimer's seconds carpenter's they live up to zack snyder's 300 and the last 2 seasons of 24 slavoj zizek is a philosopher and cultural critic whose innovative interpretations of lacan hegel and marx and piercing analyses of politics popular culture cinema and literature have earned him the status of one of the most significant and dangerous thinkers today he is a professor at the european graduate school international director of the birbeck institute for humanities university of london and a senior researcher at the institute for sociology university of ljubljana slovenia zizek is the author and editor of over thirty books most recently in defense of lost causes first as tragedy then as farce and living in the end times this lecture is made possible by a generous grant from carmen m christensen when monday october 17 2011 5 30 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where cubberley auditorium map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students tags lecture reading international visual arts sponsor department of art & art history contact 650 723 3404 risip stanford edu admission free and open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 288 28851 more info last modified october 11 2011
